### Basic Cache Operations
### Set a cache entry (plain text in body)
POST {{BaseUrl}}/cache/test_key
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello Redis!

### Get a cache entry
GET {{BaseUrl}}/cache/test_key

### Delete a cache entry
DELETE {{BaseUrl}}/cache/test_key

### Set another cache entry with different content
POST {{BaseUrl}}/cache/user:123
Content-Type: text/plain

John Doe

### Get user data
GET {{BaseUrl}}/cache/user:123

### Set JSON data as text
POST {{BaseUrl}}/cache/config:app
Content-Type: text/plain

{"theme": "dark", "version": "1.0"}

### Get JSON config
GET {{BaseUrl}}/cache/config:app

### Set a longer value
POST {{BaseUrl}}/cache/description:product:456
Content-Type: text/plain

This is a detailed product description that demonstrates how the basic cache can store longer text content with proper expiration.

### Get the description
GET {{BaseUrl}}/cache/description:product:456

### Clean up - delete all test entries
DELETE {{BaseUrl}}/cache/user:123

DELETE {{BaseUrl}}/cache/config:app

DELETE {{BaseUrl}}/cache/description:product:456
